The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Nov. 17: The Securities and Exchange Board of India will shortly revise norms for public offers and unveil a slew of products for secondary and derivative markets. ?Sebi is taking steps to streamline IPO norms to help companies compete globally and make follow-on public offers more efficient,? Sebi executive director Pratip Kar told the Indo-US economic summit here.

 New Delhi, Nov. 17: The government may simplify fringe benefit tax, rationalise tax structure and depreciation norms for R amp;D in the next budget, apart from making efforts to raise the tax-GDP ratio and garner more funds for development. 

 New Delhi, Nov. 17: The Airports Authority of India (AAI) would enter the capital market to raise resources for funding the modernisation of about 30 airports across the country, for which an estimated Rs 40,000 crore is required.

 Mumbai, Nov. 17: Eureka Forbes has entered into a 50:50 joint venture with Lux International for market expansion and product development.

 New Delhi, Nov. 17: Abandoning its attempts to push politicians on the board of Navratna companies as independent directors, the government has nominated four experts to the board of Bharat Heavy Electricals.




